{{Infobox FIBA tourney | title = 2015 FIBA COCABA Championship | subtitle = 8th Central American Basketball Championship | year = 2015 | host = {{CRC}} | dates = 16–20 September | teams = [[#Participating teams|7]] | venues = 1 | cities = 1 | champions = PAN | title_number = 3 | prevseason = [[2013 FIBA COCABA Championship|2013]] | nextseason = [[2017 FIBA COCABA Championship|2017]] }}
The '''2015 Men's [[FIBA COCABA Championship]]''' was the regional [[basketball]] championship of [[FIBA Americas]] for the [[Central America|Central American]] and [[Caribbean]] subzone. The top 3 national teams qualified to [[2016 Centrobasket]]. The tournament was held in the city of [[San José, Costa Rica|San José]], [[Costa Rica]], from 16 to 20 September 2015.
== Participating teams == * {{bk|HON}} * {{bk|GUA}} * {{bk|CRC}} * {{bk|MEX}} * {{bk|BLZ}} ''(withdrew)'' * {{bk|NCA}} * {{bk|SLV}} * {{bk|PAN}}
Costa Rica qualified as host.
== Preliminary round == The draw for the 2015 FIBA COCABA Championship was held on August 4, 2015. Eight teams were drawn into two pools with 4 teams in each.
