{{Infobox college sports rivalry | name = Chicago–Purdue football rivalry | team1_image = Chicago Maroons logo.svg | team1_image_size = | team2_image = Purdue Boilermakers logo.svg | team2_image_size = 120px | team1 = [[Chicago Maroons football|Chicago Maroons]] | team2 = [[Purdue Boilermakers football|Purdue Boilermakers]] | total_meetings = 44 | series_record = Chicago leads, 28–13–1 | first_meeting_date = November 19, 1892 | first_meeting_result = Purdue 38, Chicago 0 | last_meeting_date = October 17, 1936 | last_meeting_result = Purdue 35, Chicago 7 | largest_win_margin = Chicago, 56–0 (1907) | longest_win_streak = Chicago, 16 (1902–17) | current_win_streak = Purdue, 7 (1930–36) }}
The '''Chicago–Purdue football rivalry''' is a now defunct American [[college football]] rivalry between the [[Chicago Maroons football|Chicago Maroons]] and [[Purdue Boilermakers football|Purdue Boilermakers]]. Chicago leads the series 28–13–1.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=2199&dat=19361014&id=NQZRAAAAIBAJ&sjid=Dr8MAAAAIBAJ&pg=2087,2804600&hl=en|title=Chicago-Purdue Game May End Long Grid Rivalry|work=Lawrence Journal=World|date=October 14, 1936}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1499&dat=19361013&id=JHUxAAAAIBAJ&sjid=MiIEAAAAIBAJ&pg=2323,7997155&hl=en|title=Purdue Chicago End an Old Grid Rivalry Saturday|work=The Milwaukee Journal|date=October 13, 1936}}</ref> The series was first played in 1892.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/3385721/montana_butte_standard/|work=Montana Butte Standard|page=26|date=October 19, 1935|accessdate=October 10, 2015|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|title=Feud Frays and To Interest In Week's Tilts}} {{Open access}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/3385813/the_san_bernardino_county_sun/|work=The San Bernardino County Sun|page=15|title=Leading Teams of Big Ten Groom For Meeting With Old-Time Jinx|author=Dixon Stewart|date=November 6, 1930|accessdate=October 10, 2015|via=[[Newspapers.com]]}} {{Open access}}</ref> The rivalry has not been played since 1936.
