{{infobox country at games | NPC = CUB | NPCname = Comité Paralimpico Cubano | games = Summer Paralympics | year = 1996 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = | location = [[Atlanta, Georgia|Atlanta]] | competitors = 10 (9 men and 1 woman) | sports = | flagbearer = | rank = 23 | gold = 8 | silver = 3 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = 1992 | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }}
Ten athletes (nine men and one woman) from '''[[Cuba]]''' competed at the '''[[1996 Summer Paralympics]]''' in [[Atlanta]], [[United States]].<ref name="paralympic.org">{{Cite web|url=http://www.paralympic.org/Athletes/Results |title=Atlanta 1996 Paralympic Games: Cuba |accessdate=2012-08-27 |work=paralympic.org}}</ref> Competitors from Cuba won 11 medals, including 8 golds and 3 silvers to finish 23rd in the [[1996 Summer Paralympics medal table|medal table]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Medal Standings Atlanta 1996 Paralympic Games|url=http://www.paralympic.org/results/historical }}</ref> All their medals were won in athletics.
