{{Coord|33.748471|-84.417106|type:landmark|display=title}}

The '''Forbes Arena''' is a 6,000-seat multi-purpose [[arena]] in [[Atlanta, Georgia]], [[United States|USA]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://athletics.morehouse.edu/sports/2010/11/22/forbes.aspx?id=9|title=Morehouse College Maroon Tigers - Forbes Arena|website=athletics.morehouse.edu|language=en|access-date=2017-04-15}}</ref> It is home to the [[Morehouse College]]  Maroon Tigers [[basketball]] [[team]]. It also hosted [[Basketball at the 1996 Summer Olympics|basketball]] preliminary matches during the [[1996 Summer Olympics]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.sandiegouniontribune.com/sdut-atlantas-olympic-venues-meet-varying-fates-since-2016jul29-story.html|title=Atlanta's Olympic venues meet varying fates since 1996|last=Writer|first=PAUL NEWBERRY AP Sports|work=sandiegouniontribune.com|access-date=2017-04-15|language=en-US}}</ref> and was the home arena to the [[Atlanta Glory]]. It was opened in 1996 at a cost of $8 million. It sits adjacent to the college's old gym, Archer Hall, which seats 1,000. 

The arena was named after Franklin Forbes, an athletic director at [[Morehouse College]] and the school's first basketball coach.

