{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Franck Grandel | image = Grandel.JPG | image_size = 200 | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1978|3|17}} | birth_place = [[Pointe-à-Pitre]], [[Guadeloupe]] | height = {{height|m=1.84|precision=0}} | position = [[Goalkeeper (football)|Goalkeeper]] | currentclub = | clubnumber = | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 1999–2001 | years2 = 2001–2003 | years3 = 2003–2004 | years4 = 2004–2005 | years5 = 2005–2008 | years6 = 2009–2011 | years7 = 2011–2013 | years8 = 2013–2015 | years9 = 2013–2017 | years10 = 2017 | clubs1 = [[Besançon RC]] | clubs2 = [[FC Libourne-Saint-Seurin]] | clubs3 = [[Skoda Xanthi]] | clubs4 = [[Troyes AC]] | clubs5 = [[FC Utrecht]] | clubs6 = [[Dijon FCO]] | clubs7 = [[USL Dunkerque]] | clubs8 = [[Troyes AC|Troyes B]] | clubs9 = [[Troyes AC|Troyes]] | clubs10 = → [[US Boulogne|Boulogne]] (loan) | caps1 = 15 | caps2 = 64 | caps3 = 16 | caps4 = 22 | caps5 = 27 | caps6 = 8 | caps7 = 47 | caps8 = 17 | caps9 = 2 | caps10 = 1 | goals1 = 0 | goals2 = 0 | goals3 = 0 | goals4 = 0 | goals5 = 0 | goals6 = 0 | goals7 = 0 | goals8 = 0 | goals9 = 0 | goals10 = 0 | nationalyears1 = 2007–2012 | nationalteam1 = [[Guadeloupe national football team|Guadeloupe]] | nationalcaps1 = 22 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | club-update = 19 December 2015 (UTC) | ntupdate = 25 January 2009 }}
'''Franck Grandel''' (born 17 March 1978) is a [[Guadeloupean]] retired footballer.
==Club career== Grandel is a goalkeeper who was born in [[Pointe-à-Pitre]], [[Guadeloupe]], and made his debut in professional football, being part of the [[Skoda Xanthi]] squad, in the 2003-04 season. He has also played for [[Besançon RC]], [[FC Libourne Saint-Seurin]] and [[Troyes AC]], before joining FC Utrecht, in 2005. Grandel was released from his contract with FC Utrecht in November 2007 <sup><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fcutrecht.nl/actueel/nieuws/447 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-07-24 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071218070022/http://www.fcutrecht.nl/actueel/nieuws/447/ |archivedate=18 December 2007 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>{{nl|icon}}</sup>.
He signed a two-year contract with French [[Ligue 2]] side [[Dijon FCO]] just before the [[2009 CONCACAF Gold Cup]].<ref>[http://www.dfco.fr/ Arrivent au DFCO :] - Dijon FCO</ref>
==International career== During the [[2007 CONCACAF Gold Cup]], when [[Guadeloupe national football team|Guadeloupe]] surprisingly advanced to the tournament semifinals, Grandel was given top goalkeeper award and was also named to the tournament All-star team. He had to leave the 2009 Gold Cup squad because of injury.<ref>[http://www.goldcup.org/page/GoldCup/NewsDetail/0,,12802~1713729,00.html Grandel, three others out of Guadeloupe with injuries] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090707014509/http://www.goldcup.org/page/GoldCup/NewsDetail/0%2C%2C12802~1713729%2C00.html |date=7 July 2009 }} - Gold Cup 2009</ref>
