{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}} {{Infobox Stadium |stadium_name = Bijeljina City Stadium |image =<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Gradski Stadion Bijeljina.jpg|270px]] --> |fullname = |location = [[Bijeljina]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]] |capacity = 6,000(for football matches) 8,000(concerts) |tenants = [[FK Radnik Bijeljina|Radnik]] |}} '''Bijeljina Gradski Stadion''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Bijeljina]], [[Republika Srpska]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and is the home ground of [[FK Radnik Bijeljina]]. The stadium holds 6,000 people. The record attendance was on the concert of [[Željko Joksimović]] where 8,000 people were watching the show.
==Concerts and events== * [[Dragana Mirković]] – 15 July 2010 * [[Miroslav Ilić]] – 6 June 2013 * [[Željko Joksimović]] – 8 August 2013 {{small|(8,000 people in attendance)}}
