{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2014}} {{Malay name|Reduan|Petara}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Reduan Petara | fullname = Reduan bin Haji Petara | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1988|05|25|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Brunei]] | height = {{convert|1.83|m|abbr=on}} | position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]] | currentclub = [[DPMM FC]] | clubnumber = 5 | youthyears1 = 2007–2008 | youthclubs1 = [[March United]] | years1 = 2009–2011 | years2 = 2012–2014 | years3 = 2015– | caps1 = | goals1 = | caps2 = | goals2 = | caps3 = 14 | goals3 = 0 | clubs1 = [[AM Gunners]] | clubs2 = [[Indera SC]] | clubs3 = [[DPMM FC]] | nationalyears1= 2007–2014 | nationalcaps1=10 | nationalgoals1=1 | nationalteam1= [[Brunei national under-21 football team|Brunei U21]] | nationalyears2= 2011 | nationalcaps2=3 | nationalgoals2=1 | nationalteam2= [[Brunei national under-23 football team|Brunei U23]] | nationalyears3= 2012– | nationalcaps3= 6 | nationalgoals3= 0 | nationalteam3 = [[Brunei national football team|Brunei]] | club-update = 28 May 2018 | ntupdate = 9 March 2016 }}
'''Reduan bin Haji Petara''' (born 25 May 1988) is a [[Brunei]]an international [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[DPMM FC]] and the [[Brunei national football team|Brunei national team]] as a [[defender (association football)|defender]].
Reduan started playing club football with the youth team of [[March United]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Winning start for PIP|url=http://www.bt.com.bn/classification/sport/2007/07/23/winning_start_for_pip|date=23 July 2007|publisher=[[The Brunei Times]]|accessdate=9 March 2016}}</ref> He transferred to [[AM Gunners]] of the [[Brunei Premier League]] in 2009, his defensive displays helped his club to finish third.<ref>{{cite web |title=AM Gunners fire late salvo |url=http://www.bt.com.bn/sport-national/2009/12/22/am-gunners-fire-late-salvo|date=22 December 2009|publisher=[[The Brunei Times]]|accessdate=9 March 2016}}</ref> After AM Gunners disbanded, he joined [[Indera SC]] and won the newly-formed [[Brunei Super League]] twice in a row.<ref>{{cite web |title=Mohd Aqmal comes to Indera's rescue|url=http://www.bt.com.bn/2012/12/17/mohd-aqmal-comes-inderas-rescue|date=17 December 2012|publisher=[[The Brunei Times]]|accessdate=9 March 2016}}</ref>
Reduan signed with Brunei's professional club [[Brunei DPMM FC|DPMM FC]] at the start of the [[2015 S.League]] season.<ref>{{cite web |title=DPMM FC set for Thai friendlies|url=http://www.bt.com.bn/sports-national/2015/02/01/dpmm-fc-set-thai-friendlies|date=1 February 2015|publisher=The Brunei Times|accessdate=9 March 2016}}</ref> He only appeared twice in his debut season as DPMM won the S.League championship for the first time.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sergio Stars To Help Wasps Clinch First-Ever Title|url=http://www.sleague.com/match-report/s-league/2015/November/2015-11-21/brunei-dpmm-fc|date=22 November 2015|publisher=[[S.League]]|accessdate=9 March 2016}}</ref>
==International career== Reduan played in three editions of the [[Hassanal Bolkiah Trophy]] for the [[Brunei national under-21 football team|Brunei under-21s]]. His first tournament was in [[2007 Hassanal Bolkiah Trophy|2007]] where he started in all three of Brunei's games.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hassanalbolkiahtrophy.com.bn/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=15&Itemid=29|title=Hassanal Bolkiah Trophy - TEAM MEMBERS|publisher=Information Department, Prime Minister's Office of Brunei|date=6 February 2007|deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071103190917/http://www.hassanalbolkiahtrophy.com.bn/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=15&Itemid=29|archivedate=3 November 2007|accessdate=10 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hassanalbolkiahtrophy.com.bn/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=23&Itemid=37|title=Hassanal Bolkiah Trophy - PREVIOUS MATCHES|publisher=Information Department, Prime Minister's Office of Brunei|date=7 February 2007|deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071103190958/http://www.hassanalbolkiahtrophy.com.bn/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=23&Itemid=37|archivedate=3 November 2007|accessdate=10 March 2016}}</ref> His second was in [[2012 Hassanal Bolkiah Trophy|2012]] when the hosts won the trophy for the first time, though he was overlooked in the final match for [[Hazwan Hamzah]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Brunei shortlists 22-man HBT squad|url=http://www.bt.com.bn/sports-national/2012/02/02/brunei-shortlists-22-man-hbt-squad|date=2 January 2012|publisher=[[The Brunei Times]]|accessdate=10 March 2016}}</ref> He returned as one of the five permitted overage players for the [[2014 Hassanal Bolkiah Trophy|2014 edition]] for an unsuccessful defence of the trophy.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coach Kwon happy with Brunei’s grouping|url=http://www.bt.com.bn/sports-national/2014/07/13/coach-kwon-happy-brunei%E2%80%99s-grouping|date=13 July 2014|publisher=[[The Brunei Times]]|accessdate=10 March 2016}}</ref> He played for the [[Brunei national under-23 football team|under-23s]] at the [[Football at the 2011 Southeast Asian Games|2011 SEA Games]], scoring the winner against [[Philippines national under-23 football team|Philippines]] in the group stage.
Reduan's full international debut for the [[Brunei national football team|Wasps]] came on 26 September 2012 in a friendly against [[Indonesia national football team|Indonesia]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Hat-Trick Irfan Bachdim Hantam Brunei Darussalam|url=http://www.goal.com/id-ID/news/1387/nasional/2012/09/27/3405055/hat-trick-irfan-bachdim-hantam-brunei-darussalam|date=27 September 2012|publisher=Goal.com|accessdate=27 May 2015}}</ref> He made further appearances at the [[2014 AFF Championship qualification|2014]] [[AFF Suzuki Cup]] qualifying round and the [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC First Round|2018 World Cup qualifying first round for AFC]].<ref>{{cite web |title=World Cup dreams over|url=http://www.bt.com.bn/sports-national/2015/03/18/world-cup-dreams-over|date=18 March 2015|publisher=[[The Brunei Times]]|accessdate=10 March 2016}}</ref>
